    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{2}{x^{2}-5x-50}-\frac{x-8}{x^{2}-5x-50}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{1}{x+5}, x\ne 10</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{2}{x^{2}-5x-50}-\frac{x-8}{x^{2}-5x-50}} 
      \amp = \frac{{2-\left(x-8\right)}}{{x^{2}-5x-50}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{2-x+8}}{{\left(x-10\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+5\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-x+10}}{{\left(x-10\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+5\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-\left(x-10\right)}}{{\left(x-10\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+5\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{1}{x+5}, x\ne 10}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>x-10</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>x \ne {10}</m>.</p>
</solution>
